The South African Weather Service (Saws) has warned of possible scattered showers and thundershowers expected across KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday afternoon. The weather agency said they are expecting strong damaging winds which may lead to falling trees blocking minor roads and could result to injuries due to flying debris. Hail leading to damage to infrastructure, settlements, property, vehicles, livelihood and livestock is also expected. Saws said there also might be flooding of susceptible roads, low lying areas and bridges. Areas expected to be affected are Abaqulusi, Big Five Hlabisa - Hlabisa, Big Five Hlabisa - Hluhluwe, Dr N. Dlamini-Zuma - Underberg, Ethekwini, Greater Kokstad, Impendle, Ingwe, Jozini, KwaDukuza, Mandeni, Maphumulo, Mkhambathini, Mpofana - Giants Castle, Mpofana - Mooi River, Msinga, Mthonjaneni, Mtubatuba, Ndwedwe, Nkandla, Nongoma, Nquthu, Ray Nkonyeni - Paddock & Margate, Richmond, The Msunduzi, Ubuhlebezwe, Ulundi, Umdoni - Dumisa & Pennigton, uMfolozi, uMhlathuze RB & Ntambanana, Umhlabuyalingana, uMlalazi, uMngeni, uMshwathi, UMuziwabantu, Umvoti, Umzimkhulu, Umzumbe and uPhongolo. The public is advised to avoid outdoor activities and if you are outdoors during the storm, you are advised to seek shelter immediately but not under a tree, telephone lines or power lines. “If possible, stay indoors well clear of windows, shelter pets, cover vehicles and disconnect electrical appliances,” warned the weather service.